-- VW to End Work Early for Germany-Greece Soccer Game, Bild Says
-- B y   C h r i s t i a n   W u e s t n e r
-- 2012-06-21T07:23:59Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-21/vw-to-end-work-early-for-germany-greece-soccer-game-bild-says.html
Volkswagen AG (VOW)  will shut its German
factories earlier than normal tomorrow, to let employees watch
the European championship quarterfinal soccer match between
Germany and  Greece ,  Bild Zeitung  reported.  The early closedown will affect the company’s  headquarters
in Wolfsburg and plants in Braunschweig, Emden, Hannover,
Kassel, Salzgitter and Zwickau, the newspaper said.  General
Motors Co. (GM) ’s German subsidiary, Opel, will end its evening shift
two hours earlier, Bild reported.  At  Daimler AG (DAI) , the factories are free to decide whether to
stop production before the usual time, the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Christian Wuestner in Berlin at 
 cwuestner@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
